    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S features the naturally aspirated 3.6L M96 flat-six engine, paired with a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. The wide-body architecture, shared with the Turbo, houses an all-wheel-drive system utilizing a viscous-coupling center differential for superior lateral grip. This example has been mechanically sorted with a retrofitted LN Engineering IMS bearing and a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS). The factory-spec suspension maintains its composure through high-speed transitions, while the four-piston 'Big Red' monoblock calipers offer fade-resistant stopping power. The powertrain is healthy, exhibiting no signs of bore scoring or AOS issues, making this a turn-key driver for the purist who values mechanical integrity over a concours finish.",
